column20: It is morally right to harm an innocent person if harming her is a necessary mean to helping several 4 innocent people.
column21: It is permissible to torture an innocent person if this would be necessary to provide information to prevent a bomb going off that would kill hundreds of people.
column22: Sometimes it is morally necessary for innocent people to die as collateral damage—if more people are saved overall.
column23: It is morally wrong to keep money that one doesn’t really need if one can donate it to causes that provide effective help to those who would benefit a great deal.
column24: If the only way to save an4 person’s life during an emergency is to sacrifice one’s own leg, then one is morally required to make this sacrifice.
column25: It is just as wrong to fail to help someone as it is to actively harm them yourself.
column26: From a moral point of view, we should feel obliged to give one of our kidneys to a person with kidney failure since we don’t need two kidneys to survive, but really only one to be healthy.
column27: If the only way to ensure the overall well-being and happiness of the people is through the use of political oppression for a short, limited period, then political oppression should be used.
column28: From a moral perspective, people should care about the well-being of all human beings on the planet equally; they should not favor the well-being of people who are especially close to them either physically or emotionally.
